</details>
<ingredients><ingredient amount="1.0 Pound">Beef</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0">Onion</ingredient><ingredient amount="2.0 Ounce">Bean</ingredient><ingredient amount="15.0 Ounce">Bean</ingredient><ingredient amount="3.0 Ounce">Tomato</ingredient><ingredient amount="16.0 Ounce">Barbecue Sauce</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0 Teaspoon">Chili Powder</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0 Tablespoon">Molasses</ingredient></ingredients>
<instructions>
In a large pot or Dutch oven, brown the ground meat. Drain.
Return the cooked meat to the pot.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Stir to combine.
Cover, and simmer over medium-low heat, stirring as needed, for about 1-2 hours.
</instructions>
